The paper deals with capacity and delay scaling in wireless networks, which is a topic that falls under the intersection of several sub-fields in computer science. However, based on the abstract, it is most likely that the paper belongs to the Information Theory (cs.IT) sub-category, as it mentions the derivation of capacity scaling laws for wireless networks using spectral properties. The paper also deals with network models and graph theory, which are relevant to the Networked Systems (cs.NI) and Social and Information Networks (cs.SI) sub-categories. The mention of "scaling laws" suggests that the paper may also belong to the Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing (cs.DS) sub-category. Finally, the paper mentions the evaluation of bounds for specific graph topologies, which could place it in the Mathematical Aspects of Computer Science (cs.MA) sub-category.
